Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, and hot pepper sauce in a bowl until smoothly combined; spread mixture in an even layer over a large plate. Spread salsa in a layer over the cream cheese mixture. Combine tomato, green pepper, and green onions in a bowl and spread the vegetables over the salsa. Cover the dip with Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate until serving time; remove from refrigerator about 20 minutes before serving to allow cream cheese mixture to soften.